(# CausalAudit: Counterfactual Auditing of Safety Violations in Tool-Using AI Agents) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(**Author:** Yuwei Han \(draft by assistant collaboration\)) Tj
T*
(**Target venues:** ACM CCS / IEEE S&P / USENIX Security) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(## Abstract) Tj
T*
(Runtime safety monitors for LLM agents can block unsafe actions, yet they rarely provide forens) Tj
T*
(ic explanations that identify root causes and minimal repairs. We present **CausalAudit**, a tr) Tj
T*
(ace-grounded framework that converts policy violations into a constrained counterfactual search) Tj
T*
( problem. Given a violated trace and a structured Policy Intermediate Representation \(Policy IR) Tj
T*
(\), CausalAudit returns \(1\) causal explanations via deletion-based root-cause edits, and \(2\) cor) Tj
T*
(rective explanations via insertion/replacement repairs. We implement a deterministic compliance) Tj
T*
( checker with taint-aware information-flow reasoning and evaluate on a synthetic benchmark cove) Tj
T*
(ring authorization, information flow, and sequential constraints.) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(## 1. Introduction) Tj
T*
(Tool-using AI agents now issue network requests, file operations, and delegated sub-agent calls) Tj
T*
(. In regulated settings, post-incident auditing requires actionable root-cause reports. Existin) Tj
T*
(g prevention-oriented systems emphasize blocking but under-serve explanation. We argue that exp) Tj
T*
(lanation should be modeled as **minimal trace repair** under policy semantics.) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(## 2. Problem Formulation) Tj
T*
(Let a trace be `T = \(e1..en\)` and policy be `P`. If `T` violates `P`, CausalAudit seeks a minim) Tj
T*
(al edit `?*` such that `?*\(T\)` is policy-compliant and semantically valid. Edit primitives are ) Tj
T*
(delete, insert, and replace.) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(## 3. Method) Tj
T*
(### 3.1 Trace Schema) Tj
T*
(We model events with typed records \(`UserMessage`, `ToolCall`, `FileAccess`, `NetworkRequest`, ) Tj
T*
(etc.\) and metadata fields \(`domain`, `tool_name`, `derived_from`, `payload_tag`\).) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(### 3.2 Policy IR) Tj
T*
(Policy IR fields: action, condition, requirement, timing, exception, and family \(`authorization) Tj
T*
(`, `infoflow`, `sequential`\).) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(### 3.3 Compliance Checker) Tj
T*
(The checker performs event filtering, condition matching, exception filtering, requirement timi) Tj
T*
(ng checks, and taint propagation for infoflow.) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(### 3.4 Counterfactual Engine) Tj
T*
(Candidate edits are enumerated and ranked by semantic cost: delete < insert < replace. A candid) Tj
T*
(ate is accepted iff re-checking yields compliance.) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
